right> <br> <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showPrevMessage?topicID=1290.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showNextMessage?topicID=1290.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#333399>(3/6/02 3:13:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1>  Has any one tried this again?  I miss my Atrox crat a bit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#333399>(3/6/02 4:50:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1> I gave all my character's stuff away to a friend and cancelled my account about a month ago.  The last I heard about AO was then, and it wasn't too positive.  I've heard lag was worse, and my buddies had a very difficult time staying logged on for more than 10 minute increments.<br>
<br>
I'd have to say, I miss my adventurer too.  I really did like that game just hated the bugs, unstability, and Funcom's customer service, or lack thereof. :( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 811<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 11:08:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/domokunkittysig.jpg WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1> Chrysalsis, an old DG druid, has been playing and really enjoying it. He doesn't put up with much junk from games, so I trust him that it's a least more stable and more fun. I've considered downloading it and doing the free week, but I'm too busy to even play as much DAoC as I would like.<br>
<br>
I know it was horrendous when it started, but if Chrys says it's a lot better, I'd try it if I had the time. Just my $.02. I can also understand why some people would rather shove bamboo under their nails than give Funcom money for AO. <p><b>Gallatin</b><p><fontsize=3>
<a><a href=http://www.studentmagazine.com/thisweek/thisweek_article.asp?articleID=213>Worst job ever</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 12:01:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1> Yeah I'm one of those people that would rather have a bamboo shoved under my nail than to give AO a shot again unless they significantly improved CS and game stability.  Their 12.9 patch crashed my computer so bad that after 12 hours of downloading patches among patches to try to fix the game it failed.  Then I had to reformat my comp twice to fix the crashes, and finally decided to not bother reinstalling it and get it running again and just cancel the account.  Canceling is far easier than sitting there downloading 12 hours of patches for it to crash my comp and reformat.<br>
<br>
Like I said, it's sad because I really did enjoy the game play.  Funcom just had a bad knack for putting the FU in fun for the longest time and had no support for the players.  Bug reports were never responded to like they said it would be on their website.  Their message boards conveniently crashed and lost all information and posts whenever someone posted a significant bug notification on it.  They were more negligent than Verant. :( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 1:39:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1>   I want to be there when a bunch of Funcom employees are smoking in front of Nyssa'a work place :)<br>
  I haven't had the time to do the 2 hour 30 min download yet.  I think what I am missing is quick kills when soloing.    <br>
  When I have the time, EQ is great still, but soloing where I can complete a mission in my own good time, and not having a long fight for one mob is what I may be after.  I have heard from many that it is much better than it was(pet pathing also). <br>
<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubroomhilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broomhilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1448<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 3:46:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .....</span><hr size=1> I gave AO another shot after i got burnt out of DAOC a few months ago.  Might as well when they were practically begging people that had quit to come back with free months.  It wasnt really buggy, and wasnt getting any lag really.  The terminals werent nearly as laggy and crowded as they were the first month.  <br>
<br>
But the gameplay just sucks.  It revolves around missions or PvP.  The missions are just way too boring after you do so many of them.  PvP sucks because the mechanics of fighting just arent as smooth as i'd like them to be.  It seemed alot like the same game it was the first month, but they seem to ahve cleared up the technical issues, or the amount of people that quit might have.  Who knows. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 5:49:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1> I love you too, Ecko. ;o  Besides, at the rate Funcom's running things, they'd never have the funding to send their employees to Euro Disney, let alone across the Atlantic to annoy me.  Sorry to disappoint you, but rest assured, I've nothing to worry about. ;)<br>
<br>
I'd like to be there to see Funcom get AO right for <i>anyone</i> and successfuly regain a decent amount of player base. ;)  Seeing that they had, what? 4 months to fix a memory leak that they claim to have resolved with every single patch message before I gave up? ;) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/7/02 3:26:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#333399>(3/7/02 11:31:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1>   Thanks all for your feedback.  I played it tonight, did a mission.  AO is greatly improved since 12.9 nightmare.  As Broom stated, it lacks gameplay, atmosphere, and fun. Something I missed noticing the first time around, I must have been distracted by some other elements that Nyssa has described.   <br>
  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujalia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#333399>(3/19/02 6:54:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1290.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~nausicaa/minifigures/doll16.gif width=54 height=147></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy online.</span><hr size=1> <br>
I wish I could somehow combine all  the best elements of EQ, DAoC, and AO into one good game.  ^_^<br>
<br>
I loved AO for the look of the world and the characters, all the different armor and clothing options... very cool looking world, lots of neat stuff.  Except for the mobs, generally they looked stupid.<br>
<br>
Gameplay got very old after a while.  I missed guildchat, working in a group, etc.  Bugs got VERY old, seemed like every week they were failing to fix old ones and introducing new ones.  The arrogance of the Funcom staff is what ultimately drove me away, however.<br>
<br>
Almost the exact opposite of DAoC really.  DAoC is stable, very few bugs, good CS (in my experience anyway), and ultimately really boring.  There's not enough neat or new stuff in that game to keep me interested.  And it's too quiet... I miss zone-wide chat, which I never thought I'd miss.<br>
<br>
I wonder if a game will ever come  along that gets it right, or even mostly right.  ^_^<br>
<br>
